gov.usgs.anss.picker

Class JsonDetectionSender

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.picker.JsonDetectionSender

  • public class JsonDetectionSender
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements various ways a JSON message can be configuration to be Sent out. Initial version just makes file on a path. 
     -json method1&method2&method3
 
 where each method consists of key;arg1;arg2;arg3...
 
 method      Format
 path       path;[SOME PATH TO DIRECTORY] - write JSON methods as files on this path
 kafka      kafka;type;server:port
            type matches detection-formats like 'beam' or 'pick'
            server is like : 'igskcicgvmkafka.cr.usgs.gov/9092' Note: slash is changed to ':' in the server tags

        public boolean sendPick(java.lang.String pickID,
                        java.lang.String overrideTopic,
                        java.lang.String agency,
                        java.lang.String author,
                        java.util.GregorianCalendar pickTime,
                        java.lang.String seedname,
                        double amplitude,
                        double period,
                        java.lang.String phase,
                        double error_window,
                        java.lang.String polarity,
                        java.lang.String onset,
                        java.lang.String pickerType,
                        double hipassFreq,
                        double lowpassFreq,
                        double snr)
        Write a pick to disk via this object. The return indicates whether the pick was written to disk. This call omits all beam and associated parameters.
        Parameters:
        pickID - If this is updating a pickID, provide it.
        overrideTopic - If not null, this overrides the kafka topic
        agency - Character string with agency id
        author - Character string with author name
        pickTime - The time of the pick
        seedname - NNSSSSSCCCLL for the channel being picked
        amplitude - in um (<=0. omit) must have this to create an amplitude with period
        period - in seconds (<=0. omit)
        phase - A phase code like "P" or "S" limit 8 characters (null omit)
        error_window - This is the error window half width (<0 omit)
        polarity - up or down (null omit)
        onset - impulsive, emergent, questionable (null omit)
        pickerType - manual, raypicker, lomax, earthworm, other. (null omit) We can add others if we need them
        hipassFreq - Frequency in Hz of high pass filter on picker (<=0. omit) to have a Filter entry one frequency must not be omited
        lowpassFreq - Frequency in Hz of low pass filter on picker (<=0. omit)
        snr - The estimated signal to noise ratio (<=0. omit);
        Returns:
        True if the pick was written, otherwise the pick was not written and user might want to resubmit later!

        Write a pick to disk via this object. The return indicates whether the pick was written to disk. This call includes beam, but does not include associated parameters.
        Parameters:
        pickID - If this is updating a pickID, provide it.
        overrideTopic - If not null, this overrides the kafka topic
        agency - Character string with agency id
        author - Character string with author name
        pickTime - The time of the pick
        seedname - NNSSSSSCCCLL for the channel being picked
        amplitude - in um (<=0. omit) must have this to create an amplitude with period
        period - in seconds (<=0. omit)
        phase - A phase code like "P" or "S" limit 8 characters (null omit)
        error_window - This is the error window half width (<0 omit)
        polarity - up or down (null omit)
        onset - impulsive, emergent, questionable (null omit)
        pickerType - manual, raypicker, lomax, earthworm, other. (null omit) We can add others if we need them
        hipassFreq - Frequency in Hz of high pass filter on picker (<=0. omit) to have a Filter entry one frequency must not be omited
        lowpassFreq - Frequency in Hz of low pass filter on picker (<=0. omit)
        snr - The estimated signal to noise ratio (<=0. omit);
        backazm - Beam back azimuth in degress (<=0. omit) To have a beam you must have a backazm.
        backazmErr - Beam back azimuth error estimate in degrees(<=0. omit)
        slowness - Beam Slowness value(<=0. omit)
        slownessErr - Beam slowness error(<=0. omit)
        powerRatio - Beam power ratio(<=0. omit)
        powerRatioErr - Beam power error estimate (<=0. omit)
        Returns:
        True if the pick was written, otherwise the pick was not written and user might want to resubmit later!
